{
  "stem": "11144.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So when we-- when we left Lodz and we moved to Legnica, it was again-- I went in as a Jew, and, you know-- and again, the same thing happened there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were a few Jewish kids in the class.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And again, they were called names and, you know, picked and whatever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I again looked at that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as much as I wanted to be myself, I said, I can't take it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I started again going to church.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I started going to religion.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I started being ashamed I was Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and-- until-- that was from 1945 till 1951.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No, till 19-- yeah, till 1951 I was denying Jewishness.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "When we had to register to get our papers in Poland, to get the document, like a passport-type of a document, the same like in Russia, I pressured my mother to change her parents' names so the passports-- so the documents are not going to be sounding too Jewish.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, that we were observing Catholic holidays.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, because I made everybody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I put a lot of pressure on everybody.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, my stepfather was a very assimilated person.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, he was-- religion was very, very far from-- you know, from whatever.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, he did not-- he came from a very secular home.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "His parents were very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Engelberg.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, but I put pressure on-- on everybody, and I stopped associating with Jewish kids.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I was only associating with Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was until 1951.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother was really pressuring me into, you know, not going out with Poles.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
